July 28 at 11:13 AM ·

Hello Twin Cities! Check out these 9 amazing schools that deserve more credit that they get.

https://blog.schoolsparrow.com/2020/07/17/9-of-the-best-elementary-schools-in-the-twin-cities-area-schoolsparrows-hidden-gems/

Most school ranking sites overlook these schools, and in doing so, they steer families towards mostly white, highly affluent schools in Minnesota. But we're dedicated to expanding the definition of what a "good" school is. These schools are re-defining educational excellence!

Lake Harriet Lower Elementary, Lake Harriet Community School News, Oakdale Elementary, Oakdale Elementary PTA ISD 622, Monroe Elementary PTO, Dowling Elementary, Weaver Elementary, Hennepin Schools,

post_text:
Hello NCS families! This past week student council has been holding a Takis and lemonade fundraiser during lunch for the whole school. They were raising money for a homeless shelter in Minneapolis that has directly effected some of the families here at NCS. We raised a total if $451.71 in just 3 days!!! I am so proud of our students and what they have accomplished.
We have also been having a food drive this week. There will be an announcement later on today/this week of how many food items we will be dropping off along with the money we raised. Keep up the great work New Century!

post_text: The Girls on the Run twin cities event is scheduled for this Sunday, 11/10 at 7:30 at the Mall of America. Our young girls, their mentors and buddies worked hard to prepare for this main event. Girls on the Run is not just about running but is a comprehensive program with a well -developed curriculum that provides the girls with the knowledge, skills and disposition necessary for their overall growth and development. The program entails helping the girls develop the character and confidence to become productive members of the society. We will meet at the school on Sunday at 7:00 as we plan to provide a bus. Please let Ms. Nimco know if you plan to come.

post_text:
WELCOME New Century families!

New Century School (NCS) is a K-8 STEM School located in the Midway area of St. Paul, Minnesota.

Our inquiry-based learning model and multi-disciplinary instructional approach provides the foundation for our school's rigorous STEM-based curriculum.

OUR MISSION is to provide a high-quality education to nurture and inspire a community of learners through an innovative, holistic approach to education that embeds science and technology.

OUR PROGRAM acknowledges and maintains each student's individual background and prepares them for life as successful members of our diverse and technologically advancing society.

JOIN US as we offer our students a new way to learn, explore and excel with our: STEM Curriculum, Computational Thinking, Small Class Size, College and Career Prep, Engineering & Robotics, Inquiry-Based Learning, Language Support, and Extended Day Programs.

Contact us TODAY! 1380 Energy Lane, Suite 108, St. Paul, MN 55108
(651) 478-4535 or (651) 214-0157
admin@newcenturyschool.net
